A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 10 of Title 45 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to codes of ethics for government service, so as to provide a definition of "formal
3 charges" regarding ethical violations by members of certain boards, commissions, or
4 authorities; to provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date; to repeal
5 conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Article 1 of Chapter 10 of Title 45 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
9 codes of ethics for government service, is amended by revising Code Section 45-10-4,
10 relating to code of ethics for members of boards, commissions, and authorities â€” hearing,
11 notice, removal of member from office, filling vacancies, and judicial review, as follows:
12 "45-10-4.
13 (a) As used in this Code section, the term 'formal charge' means a statement made under
14 oath by an elected state, county, or municipal official, which alleges that probable cause
15 exists to believe that a member serving on a board, commission, or authority created by
