16 general statute has committed an ethical violation relative to one or more provisions of
17 Code Section 45-10-3.
18 (b) Upon formal charges being filed with the Governor relative to a violation of Code
19 Section 45-10-3 on the part of a member of any such board, commission, or authority, the
20 Governor or his or her designated agent shall conduct a hearing for the purpose of receiving
21 evidence relative to the merits of such charges. The member so charged shall be given at
22 least 30 days' notice prior to such hearing. If such charges are found to be true, the
23 Governor shall forthwith remove such member from office and the vacancy shall be filled
24 as provided by law. Such hearing shall be held in accordance with Chapter 13 of Title 50,
25 the 'Georgia Administrative Procedure Act,' and judicial review of any such decision shall
26 be in accordance with such chapter."
27 SECTION 2.
28 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
29 without such approval.
30 SECTION 3.
31 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
